Gwedolyn Mickle

June Thorne

Many members of the Department of Planning
contributed to the development of the
inventory, text, and production of this book.

The Baltimore Harbor Book was prepared
under the management of David Carroll, Chief,
Coastal Resources Planning Section.

The following people, over the past several
years, were responsibile for the significant effort
required to produce this book.

Inventory and Text:
David Habert
Deborah Holmes
Michael Lake

Elliot Lieberman

Planning and Urban Design
Anand Bhandari, Chief, Urban Design Section

Alden Christie

Ernie Caldwell

Don Duncan

Frank Fallano - Design
Carmelle Gibbons - Design
James Hall

Jay Steinhour - Design

Gerald Elkins, Production Supervisor

Production Staff:
Michael Addison
Don Frock

John Holley

Special thanks are accorded to many people
responsible for typing, editing, and proofing the
text. '

Kathy Boone
Margie Jones
Marian Laster
Nancy Mclaughlin
Jean Reynolds

The Waterfront Center prepared the chapter on
the Inner Harbor and reviewed text and format
of the Harbor Book.

The Department of Planning also wishes to
express special thanks to the Maryland Port
Administration and the Peale Museum for
providing valuable photographs, technical
information and assistance.
